            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 py-2">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">
                Full Data Ownership
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Your contact data, email templates, and analytics stay on your
                infrastructure. No vendor lock-in, no data sharing, no surprises.
                You control your data, your privacy, and your compliance posture.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 py-2">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">
                Multi-Tenant Architecture
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Agencies and SaaS platforms need workspace isolation. Notifuse
                provides complete multi-tenancy with separate databases, custom
                domains, and API keys per workspace—Customer.io requires
                separate accounts per client.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 py-2">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">
                Data Feeds for Dynamic Content
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Notifuse's unique data feeds pull real-time content from your
                APIs at send time—product recommendations, pricing, inventory
                levels, or any dynamic data. Global feeds cache data for all
                recipients, while per-recipient feeds personalize each email.
                Customer.io doesn't offer this capability.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 py-2">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">
                Choose Your ESP
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Connect to Amazon SES, Mailgun, Postmark, SendGrid, Mailjet,
                SparkPost, or any SMTP provider. Negotiate your own rates, use
                different providers for transactional vs. marketing, and switch
                anytime without changing platforms.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 py-2">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">
                Built-in Blog with AI
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Run a full blog alongside your email platform—with Liquid
                theming, SEO optimization, and an AI agent that can write,
                optimize, and edit content with web research capabilities.
                Customer.io has no blog feature.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="mt-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-orange-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-8"
          >
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 text-center">
              Ready to try Notifuse?
            </h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-6">
              Get started in minutes with Docker or one-click deployment.
              Import your contacts via CSV and start sending.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
              <a
                href="https://demo.notifuse.com/console/signin?email=demo@notifuse.com"
                class="bg-primary text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-md text-base font-semibold hover:bg-primary/80 transition-colors text-center"
              >
                Try Live Demo
              </a>
              <a
                href="https://docs.notifuse.com/installation"
                class="border border-gray-200 bg-white text-gray-700 px-6 py-3 rounded-md text-base font-semibold hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors text-center"
              >
                View Installation Guide
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </FeatureSection>

        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <FeatureSection id="faq" title="Frequently Asked Questions">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                How does Notifuse compare to Customer.io for email?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                For email specifically, Notifuse offers comparable capabilities:
                visual MJML builder, Liquid templating, A/B testing, dynamic
                segmentation, automations, transactional API, and webhooks. Notifuse
                also has unique features like data feeds and RFM segmentation that
                Customer.io lacks. The main difference is that Customer.io adds
                SMS, push, in-app, and WhatsApp channels on top of email.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Is Notifuse really free?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Notifuse offers two options: Notifuse Cloud, a fully managed
                service starting at $16/mo (30-day free trial, no credit card
                required), and a self-hosted deployment (open-source,
                AGPL-3.0). Both include all features with no per-profile fees.
                Full database export on demand — no lock-in.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Can Notifuse replace Customer.io?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                For email-focused use cases, yes. Notifuse covers transactional
                email, broadcast campaigns, automations, segmentation, and more.
                However, if you rely on Customer.io's SMS, push notifications,
                in-app messaging, or WhatsApp channels, Notifuse is not a
                direct replacement for those channels.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                How do the APIs compare?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Both platforms offer REST APIs with OpenAPI specifications.
                Notifuse adds a built-in SMTP bridge for legacy system
                integration. Customer.io provides SDKs in 8 languages (Node.js,
                Python, Go, iOS, Android, React Native, Flutter, Expo). Notifuse
                focuses on a clean REST API without SDKs.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                What about compliance?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Customer.io provides managed compliance certifications: SOC 2
                Type II, HIPAA (on Premium+), GDPR, CCPA, and ISO 27001. With
                Notifuse, you manage compliance yourself since you control the
                infrastructure. Notifuse includes GDPR tools (double opt-in,
                unsubscribe management, data deletion) but you're responsible
                for your own security posture.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Does Notifuse support SMS or push notifications?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                No. Notifuse is an email-focused platform. If you need SMS,
                push, in-app, or WhatsApp messaging, Customer.io or another
                multi-channel platform may be a better fit. Notifuse excels
                at doing email exceptionally well rather than spreading across
                multiple channels.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Is there enterprise support available?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Yes! Notifuse offers enterprise support with priority
                assistance, custom implementation, training, onboarding, and SLA
                guarantees. Contact us for details.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </FeatureSection>

        <!-- Final CTA -->
        <section class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="px-4 lg:px-8 py-20">
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
              <ComparisonCTA
                title="Ready to experience Notifuse?"
                description="Join developers and marketers who choose open-source email infrastructure over per-profile SaaS pricing."
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </ComparisonLayout>

      <!-- Footer -->
      <Footer />
    </div>
